:D,

A simple calculator that works with whole numbers written in C/Python.

The purpose of this implementation is only to show how a simple extension 
C/Python that can help people who are starting with C/Python.

In this cookbook show the two codes in C, the first is the pure C and 
the second is the implementation for Python.

I hope this cookbook possar help.

Usage:
>>> import pycalc
>>>
>>> help(pycalc)
Help on module pycalc:

NAME
    pycalc

FILE
    /home/nycholas/project/o_lalertom/nycholas/src/nycholas/trunk/code/python/c/example-1/build/lib.linux-i686-2.6/pycalc.so

FUNCTIONS
    divides(...)
        Divide two integers.
    
    multiplies(...)
        Subtracts two integers.
    
    subtract(...)
        Subtracts two integers.
    
    sum(...)
        Sum two integers.

>>>
>>> dir(pycalc)
['__doc__', '__file__', '__name__', '__package__', 'divides', 'multiplies', 'subtract', 'sum']
>>>
>>> pycalc.sum(123, 321)
444
>>>
>>> pycalc.subtract(456, 321)
135
>>>
>>> pycalc.multiplies(5, 25)
125
>>>
>>> pycalc.divides(100, 5)
20
>>>


